# Rotate touchscreen coordinates to match 90° display rotation
# (SLINT_KMS_ROTATION=90). The Steam Deck's display is natively portrait
# (800x1280) and is rotated to landscape (1280x800) by the renderer.
#
# The FTS3528 touchscreen exposes two event devices:
#   event7: "FTS3528:00 2808:1015" (ID_INPUT_TOUCHSCREEN)
#   event8: "FTS3528:00 2808:1015 UNKNOWN" (ID_INPUT_TABLET)
# Both need the calibration matrix applied.
#
# Matrix "0 1 0 -1 0 1" = 90° CCW rotation of touch input:
#   new_x = touch_y, new_y = 1 - touch_x
ACTION=="add|change", KERNEL=="event*", ATTRS{name}=="FTS3528:00 2808:1015", ENV{LIBINPUT_CALIBRATION_MATRIX}="0 1 0 -1 0 1"
ACTION=="add|change", KERNEL=="event*", ATTRS{name}=="FTS3528:00 2808:1015 UNKNOWN", ENV{LIBINPUT_CALIBRATION_MATRIX}="0 1 0 -1 0 1"
